JS Template strings (<a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/template_strings" rel="nofollow">https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/JavaScript/Refe...</a>):<p>Template strings are enclosed by the back-tick, `string text ${expression} string text`<p><pre><code>  var a = 5;
  var b = 10;
  console.log(`Fifteen is ${a + b} and not ${2 * a + b}.`);
  // &quot;Fifteen is 15 and not 20.&quot;
</code></pre>
You can also &#x27;tag&#x27; a template string:<p><pre><code>  tag`Hello ${ a + b } world ${ a * b}`;
</code></pre>
where the &#x27;tag&#x27; is a preprocessor function.
